# in __main__ block:
# 20+ tests confirming symbolic st_attention aligns with traditional transformer attention:
#   - shape: output shape == input shape (residual-compatible)
#   - causal mask: token i sees exactly tokens [0..i] (autoregressive)
#   - full attention: every token sees all tokens (bidirectional encoder)
#   - padding mask: padded tokens produce zero output, non-padded unaffected
#   - sliding window: each token attends to local window only
#   - diagonal (self-only): each token sees only itself
#   - CLS-token pattern: first token attends to all, others attend to self
#   - cross-attention pattern: query tokens attend to separate key tokens
#   - no attention (all masked): entire output is zero
#   - batch independence: different masks per batch produce independent results
#   - frame ordering: attended tokens appear in positional order (like QK^T @ V)
#   - coefficient semantics: output coeff = number of attended tokens (like attention weight sum)
#   - single token: degenerate case, output = input
#   - content preservation: merge(slice(input)) preserves original text content
#   - monotonic information growth (causal): later tokens carry more info
#   - attention sparsity: sparse mask = fewer frames in output
#   - symmetric mask: symmetric attention = same frames for symmetric tokens
#   - multi-head simulation: independent masks per batch = independent heads
#   - prefix sharing (causal): tokens sharing prefix have shared leading frames
#   - get_causal_attention_mask integration: works with the mask generator
#
# 10+ backward tests (require LLM, simple tasks for high pass rate):
#   - backward shape: grad_input.shape == input.shape
#   - backward produces symbolic content: grad_input elements are non-None
#   - typo fix propagation: LLM fixes obvious typo through backward
#   - case correction: LLM uppercases text through backward
#   - no-change identity: identical grad produces no meaningful diff
#   - multi-token causal backward: grad flows to all attended tokens
#   - partial mask backward: only attended tokens get grad
#   - multi-batch backward: independent grad per batch
#   - coefficient channel: grad_input numeric values are non-zero for attended
#   - full pipeline: forward -> manual modify output -> backward -> check grad
#   - content-aware grad: grad_input references original content in diffs
#
# 13 multi-batch storage consistency tests (no extra files, coeff-storage aligned):
#   - 1x1 minimal: single element, exact file counts
#   - 1x7 causal: single batch, 7 tokens, coefficients match frame counts
#   - 3x5 mixed masks: causal/full/empty per batch, zero-attention batch has 0 files
#   - 2x10 asymmetric padding: 8 real + 2 pad vs 2 real + 8 pad
#   - 4x3 diagonal: all self-only, all coefficients = 1.0
#   - 2x6 sliding vs full: window=2 vs full attention, different coeff patterns
#   - 3x8 multi-digit flat indices: flat indices >9 (e.g. 23 → storage/2/3/data)
#   - 5x2 sparse batches: only even batches attended, odd all zero
#   - 1x12 partial padding: 9 real + 3 pad, large single batch
#   - 2x4 return_view=True: symlink-based output, correct file and coeff counts
#   - backward 2x3 causal: grad_input file count and consistency after LLM backward
#   - backward 3x2 varied masks: full/diagonal/causal per batch, all get symbolic grad
#   - round-trip 1x5 causal: full forward→backward pipeline, input/output/grad all verified
